  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disability and Development Partners - OD Grant</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disability and Development Partners (DDP) works directly with local organisations of and for disabled people in developing countries in Africa and Asia to bring tangible changes to the lives of disabled people. It does this by developing and implementing programmes on rehabilitation, education and livelihood opportunities, advocacy and inclusion. Over the last fifteen years DDP has built up a considerable network of local partners and wide experience of disability and development issues, but it lacks capacity to leverage the learning from its work and to maximise its impact. This application aims to strengthen DDP&#x2019;s governance and management team, to create a fully accessible DDP base for nurturing new partnerships with organisations including for example, fledgling UK Diaspora groups and Disabled people&#x2019;s organisations. Alongside these two strands it intends to develop better ways of building the organisational capacity of its partners (both current and future). This includes supporting and strengthening financial management systems so they are more robust and transparent, which will then lead to better general management, growth of productive activities and increased sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
